{{Function |origin = GECK1 |summary = Adds a Topic to the Add Topic list of a Topic, creating a new choice for that Topic. |name = AddTopic |returnType = void |arguments = {{FunctionArgument |Name = TopicID |Type = ref }} |example = AddTopic HiddenCave }}
==Notes== *While Topics can also be added using the Add Topic list in the dialogue editor window, it will cause an incompatibility to any other mod that edits the Topic as this list is not merged at runtime. *This function should only be used in dialogue result scripts.
[[Category:Functions (GECK)]] [[Category:Functions]] [[Category:Dialogue Functions]] [[Category:Functions (FO3)]]

{{Function |origin = GECK1 |summary = '''AutoDisplayObjectives''' turns on or off the automatic display of objectives from the player's active quest. This is usually used in situations where the Pip-Boy is unavailable for some reason (for instance because the player's controls are partially disabled). |name = AutoDisplayObjectives |returnType = void |arguments = {{FunctionArgument |Name = iType |Type = int |Value = 0, 1 }} |example = AutoDisplayObjectives 1 }}
==See Also== *[[DisablePlayerControls]] *[[EnablePlayerControls]]
[[Category:Functions]] [[Category:Functions (GECK)]] [[Category:Quest Functions]] [[Category:Player Functions]] [[Category:Functions (FO3)]]

{{Function |origin = GECK1 |summary = Forces the game to autosave over the current autosave slot. |name = Autosave |returnType = void |example = Autosave }}
==See Also== *[[ForceSave]] *[[SaveGame]] *[[SystemSave]]
[[Category:Functions (GECK)]] [[Category:Functions]] [[Category:Miscellaneous Functions]] [[Category:Functions (FO3)]]

{{Function |origin = GECK1 |summary = Clears the enemy crime flag for a given actor's factions. All the crime-tracking factions of the designated actor will have their crime flag cleared. See [[:Category:Crime#Faction_Data|Crime]]. |name = ClearActorsFactionsPlayerEnemyFlag |returnType = void |arguments = {{FunctionArgument |Name = ActorRefID |Type = ref }} |example = ClearActorsFactionsPlayerEnemyFlag FlashREF }}
==See Also== *[[ClearFactionPlayerEnemyFlag]] *[[GetActorCrimePlayerEnemy]] *[[GetActorFactionPlayerEnemy]]
[[Category:Functions (GECK)]] [[Category:Functions]] [[Category:Crime Functions]] [[Category:Actor Functions]] [[Category:Faction Functions]] [[Category:Functions (FO3)]] [[Category:Flag Functions]]

{{Function |origin = GECK1 |summary = Resets everything related to destruction on a specified reference. Object health, model swap, model damage stages, self damage, etc. will return to the default state. |name = ClearDestruction |returnType = void |referenceType = [ObjectRefID] |example = AppleRef02.ClearDestruction }}
=='''See Also'''== *[[GetDestructionStage]] *[[OnDestructionStageChange]] *[[RemoveDestructionStage]]
[[Category:Functions (GECK)]] [[Category:Functions]] [[Category:Object Functions]] [[Category:Functions (FO3)]]

{{Function |origin = GECK1 |summary = Clears the enemy flag that gets set when a player commits a major crime against a crime-tracking faction. See [[:Category:Crime#Faction_Data|Crime]]. |name = ClearFactionPlayerEnemyFlag |returnType = void |arguments = {{FunctionArgument |Name = FactionID |Type = ref }} |example = ClearFactionPlayerEnemyFlag BigTownFaction }}
==See Also== *[[ClearActorsFactionsPlayerEnemyFlag]] *[[GetActorCrimePlayerEnemy]] *[[GetActorFactionPlayerEnemy]] *[[SetPCEnemyOfFaction]]
[[Category:Functions (GECK)]] [[Category:Functions]] [[Category:Crime Functions]] [[Category:Faction Functions]] [[Category:Savebaked Functions]] [[Category:Functions (FO3)]] [[Category:Flag Functions]]

{{Function |origin = GECK1 |summary = Resets the NoActivation sound to default. |name = ClearNoActivationSound |returnType = void |example = ClearNoActivationSound }}
==See Also== *[[SetNoActivationSound]]
[[Category:Functions]] [[Category:Functions (GECK)]] [[Category:Player Functions]] [[Category:Sound Functions]] [[Category:Functions (FO3)]]

{{Function |origin = GECK1 |summary = Marks all objectives for a quest as completed. |name = CompleteAllObjectives |returnType = void |arguments = {{FunctionArgument |Name = QuestID |Type = ref }} |example = CompleteAllObjectives MyQuest This would mark all objectives for MyQuest as complete. }}
==See Also== *[[SetObjectiveCompleted]] for details of completing an objective. *[[SetObjectiveDisplayed]]
[[Category:Functions (GECK)]] [[Category:Functions]] [[Category:Savebaked Functions]] [[Category:Quest Functions]] [[Category:Functions (FO3)]]

{{Function |origin = GECK1 |summary = Marks the quest as complete. The only real effect of this is that the quest is will be dimmed and moved below all active quests in the Pip-Boy, and will no longer be selectable as an active quest. The "Quest Completed" UI message is also displayed. |name = CompleteQuest |returnType = void |arguments = {{FunctionArgument |Name = QuestID |Type = ref }} |example = CompleteQuest MS12 }}
==See Also== *[[FailQuest]] *[[GetQuestCompleted]] *[[GetQuestCompletedAlt]] *[[GetQuestFailed]] *[[SetObjectiveCompleted]] *[[StartQuest]] *[[StopQuest]]
[[Category:Functions (GECK)]] [[Category:Functions]] [[Category:Quest Functions]] [[Category:Savebaked Functions]] [[Category:Functions (FO3)]]

{{Incomplete}} {{Function |origin = GECK1 |summary = Disables all actors. Requires a calling reference. May not take effect until cell change for actors currently loaded in cell. |name = DisableAllActors |alias = DisAA |referenceType = ref |example = player.disaa }}
==See Also== *[[DeleteReference]] / [[Zap]] *[[Enable]] *[[Reference#Enable_Parent|Enable Parent]] *[[GetDisabled]] *[[MarkForDelete]]
