Use any control code after the ":" delimiter. |name = SetEventHandler "OnControlUp:int" |arguments = {{FunctionArgument |Name = myUDF |Type = userDefinedFunction }} }}
== Example using "attack" control (4) == SetEventHandler "OnControlUp:4" MyUDF
scn MyUDF
int controlCode
begin function {controlCode}
end function
{{Control_Codes}}
==See Also== * [[OnControlDown]] * [[SetOnControlDownEventHandler]] / [[SetOnControlUpEventHandler]] (uses JIP's event handling system) * [[Event_Handling]]
[[Category:Functions_(JIP)]] [[Category:Event Handlers (JIP)]] [[Category:Input Functions]] [[Category:Event Handlers]]

{{Function |origin = LU |summary = [[Event_Handling|Event]] block type that calls the [[User_Defined_Function|UDF]] when the key is released. The released key code (int) is passed to the UDF.
Use any DirectX scancode after the ":" delimiter. |name = SetEventHandler "OnKeyUp:int" |arguments = {{FunctionArgument |Name = myUDF |Type = userDefinedFunction }} }}
== Example using "L" key == SetEventHandler "OnKeyUp:38" MyUDF
scn MyUDF
int keyCode
begin function {keyCode}
end function
{{DirectX Scancodes}}
